{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-people-page-js","path":"/speakers/tim-wallace","result":{"data":{"people":{"parent":{"html":"<h2>About</h2>\n<p>Tim Wallace is a senior editor for geography at The New York Times. He makes visual stories with information gathered from land, sky and space. He has a Ph.D. in geography from the University of Wisconsin-Madison.</p>"},"id":"d3f00cd0-a398-5d72-bf86-d4acdbbfc0d2","title":"Tim Wallace, PhD","company":"New York Times","role":"Senior Editor - Geography","twitter":null,"pronouns":null,"avatar":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/d0b996f7ab7718dcffeb7d57c2799549/1b50a/tim-wallace.jpg","srcSet":"/static/d0b996f7ab7718dcffeb7d57c2799549/c904d/tim-wallace.jpg 160w,\n/static/d0b996f7ab7718dcffeb7d57c2799549/b95ad/tim-wallace.jpg 320w,\n/static/d0b996f7ab7718dcffeb7d57c2799549/1b50a/tim-wallace.jpg 640w","sizes":"(min-width: 640px) 640px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/d0b996f7ab7718dcffeb7d57c2799549/c6aca/tim-wallace.webp 160w,\n/static/d0b996f7ab7718dcffeb7d57c2799549/0a0af/tim-wallace.webp 320w,\n/static/d0b996f7ab7718dcffeb7d57c2799549/8ae69/tim-wallace.webp 640w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 640px) 640px, 100vw"}]},"width":640,"height":640}}},"events":[{"role":"speakers","event":{"parent":{"html":"<p>We are entering an era characterized by great power conflict. Satellite imagery is shaping the face of this conflict. It is shaping the way that we monitor and deter conflict, protect civilians, prevent atrocity, support refugees and IDPs and manage supply chain disruptions. At the same time, global conflict promises to change the Space Industry which has recently enjoyed a high degree of international cooperation around our common climate threat. What do shifting patterns of international cooperation and wavering commitment to peace in space mean for our work?</p>"},"cId":"28-1345-c